[The last report mentions a suspected case of CCHF who subsequently died, and the laboratory confirmation is still pending. No history of contact with animals is mentioned though. Balochistan province of Pakistan is endemic for CCHF, and many cases travel to neighboring Sindh province for diagnosis and treatment.

In absence of an effective vaccine, taking measures to prevent exposure to the virus is the key to preventing tick-to-human, animal-to-human, and human-to-human transmission in the community. WHO recommendations to prevent CCHF are available at http://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs208/en/. - Mod.UBA

